Description.LocalizedString: A high-class ensemble that still holds the smell of London’s smoggy streets.
An Irish outfit to celebrate the holiday, gifted to Talbot by a friend in the East India Company.
An extreme overdose of putrid serum culminated in a corruption like no other. Visceral cankers blossomed through his body, sprouting from his flesh and twisting out of nearly every orifice.
Death was just the beginning of the journey.
During the Darkening, glacial winds blew from the Lost Realms, spreading an everlasting frost of penetrating ice clusters.
Organisms festered in his forgotten wounds, spreading disease from limb to limb.
He travelled to North Africa to investigate a strange new flora causing madness among the colonists.
A genius scientist with a cruel personality.
Talbot couldn't find the mice he used for his experiments.
Some could argue that the alchemist hadn’t so much destroyed his former self, as he had enhanced it.
